From e62bfd8697b8908009ba9eef2f5cbf4b2e87daa7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jake Teton-Landis <just.1.jake@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 02:28:47 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 10/25] Batch tokens are integers: serial<<1 | deferred bit, 0
 reserved for none

Replaces the object token {deferred, id} with a non-zero integer,
per the cosignal v1 spec (fact 1: currentBatchToken(): int).

- token & 1 is the deferred/urgent classification bit (the only
  documented payload); the rest is the mint serial.
- Written as serial * 2 + bit rather than a real shift so the serial
  is never truncated to 31 bits by << on long-lived pages.
- 0 is reserved for "no batch": getExternalRuntimeCurrentWriteBatch
  returns 0 when no renderer has registered a provider.
- Integer tokens cannot carry consumer WeakMap state; consumers intern
  tokens themselves (cosignal interns to 5-bit slots, spec 5.4).
